00:46:26.458 --> 00:46:28.249
<i>♪ I've been running
in circles ♪</i>

732
00:46:28.250 --> 00:46:32.957
<i>♪ You're bruising up my
heart. and I wanna show you ♪</i>

733
00:46:32.958 --> 00:46:34.707
<i>♪ I'll say it like ♪</i>

734
00:46:34.708 --> 00:46:38.332
<i>♪ Please stay cos I really
want you to want me ♪</i>

735
00:46:38.333 --> 00:46:42.500
<i>♪ You say. "OK. I really
want you to want me" ♪</i>

736
00:46:44.000 --> 00:46:47.874
<i>♪ Found you in my head
again. but it's fine ♪</i>

737
00:46:47.875 --> 00:46:52.332
Hey. here we are.
Maddie's house.

738
00:46:52.333 --> 00:46:54.416
[chuckles] Bet she's
not expecting me.

739
00:46:55.791 --> 00:46:57.166
Wait. Who do you
think Maddie is?

740
00:46:58.333 --> 00:47:01.499
[chuckles] No.
Maddie is my sister.

741
00:47:01.500 --> 00:47:02.750
and that's my mother.

742
00:47:06.166 --> 00:47:08.207
- [car door closes]
- [Nick groans]

743
00:47:08.208 --> 00:47:10.624
Oh. my God. you've gotten big!

744
00:47:10.625 --> 00:47:12.874
I still can't believe you
let her drive your car.

745
00:47:12.875 --> 00:47:15.374
Yeah. to be fair. I can't
believe it either. [chuckles]

746
00:47:15.375 --> 00:47:17.040
Can I drive it?

747
00:47:17.041 --> 00:47:19.332
I'd let you drive. I
don't know about Mum.

748
00:47:19.333 --> 00:47:21.290
I don't know how Mum
would feel about that.

749
00:47:21.291 --> 00:47:22.374
but I'd let you drive.

750
00:47:22.375 --> 00:47:24.749
[chuckles] It was not...
I was safe. I promise.

751
00:47:24.750 --> 00:47:26.457
[Nick] She was
good. She was good.

752
00:47:26.458 --> 00:47:28.540
- [Mum] No. please.
- [Noah] Let me help.

753
00:47:28.541 --> 00:47:32.040
- Are you sure? I can carry...
- Yes! Relax. I've got this.

754
00:47:32.041 --> 00:47:33.208
OK.

755
00:47:34.500 --> 00:47:37.499
[Nick] Yeah? You go
hide. Ten seconds.

756
00:47:37.500 --> 00:47:39.833
Ten. nine...

757
00:47:41.166 --> 00:47:42.582
She's great. [chuckles]

758
00:47:42.583 --> 00:47:44.499
- She's cute. isn't she?
- Yeah. [chuckles]

759
00:47:44.500 --> 00:47:47.415
We're playing hide and seek.
I've got about a minute.

760
00:47:47.416 --> 00:47:50.125
She's absolutely terrible
at it. [chuckles]

761
00:47:51.041 --> 00:47:53.791
- Your mum's great. too.
- Yeah.

762
00:47:56.541 --> 00:47:58.541
How old were you
when they split up?

763
00:47:59.750 --> 00:48:03.833
Er... she actually
left when I was 12.

764
00:48:04.875 --> 00:48:06.375
And when did you reconnect?

765
00:48:07.333 --> 00:48:10.583
Er. like. two years ago.
something like that.

766
00:48:11.833 --> 00:48:12.874
How did that...?

767
00:48:12.875 --> 00:48:14.582
All right. what is
this. an interrogation?

768
00:48:14.583 --> 00:48:16.458
Sorry. I was just curious.

769
00:48:18.375 --> 00:48:19.833
I'm joking.

770
00:48:21.500 --> 00:48:23.000
Just joking.

771
00:48:25.333 --> 00:48:27.540
The deal between me and my mum

772
00:48:27.541 --> 00:48:30.540
is that I can
continue to see Maddie

773
00:48:30.541 --> 00:48:32.583
as long as I stay
out of trouble.

774
00:48:33.125 --> 00:48:35.665
Which means no fighting.

775
00:48:35.666 --> 00:48:39.374
As long as I play by her rules.

776
00:48:39.375 --> 00:48:42.457
I get to see the most
important woman in my life.

777
00:48:42.458 --> 00:48:43.583
[chuckles]

778
00:48:44.583 --> 00:48:47.415
I don't think your girlfriend
would care to hear that.

779
00:48:47.416 --> 00:48:48.583
[chuckles]

780
00:48:50.000 --> 00:48:51.041
Who?

781
00:48:53.958 --> 00:48:56.957
I don't know. The girl
you went to the gala with?

782
00:48:56.958 --> 00:48:59.333
The one you hang with and...

783
00:49:00.375 --> 00:49:02.041
Anna and I are just friends.

784
00:49:03.666 --> 00:49:05.208
Does she know that?

785
00:49:06.583 --> 00:49:08.791
[Maddie] Nick. come find me!

786
00:49:10.041 --> 00:49:12.374
[quietly] Five? [yells] Five!

787
00:49:12.375 --> 00:49:13.541
Four!

788
00:49:14.500 --> 00:49:16.207
Three!

789
00:49:16.208 --> 00:49:18.165
Two!

790
00:49:18.166 --> 00:49:21.165
One! Ready or
not. here I come.

791
00:49:21.166 --> 00:49:23.250
- [Noah] Good luck.
- [Nick] Thank you.

792
00:49:25.125 --> 00:49:28.333
[Nick in a sing-song voice]
Maddie! Where are you?

793
00:49:28.958 --> 00:49:30.416
Just disappeared!

794
00:49:31.291 --> 00:49:32.790
- [Nick laughs]
- [Maddie squeals]

795
00:49:32.791 --> 00:49:34.707
[Maddie] Yeah. it
looks like confetti.

796
00:49:34.708 --> 00:49:36.249
[Noah] It does
look like confetti.

797
00:49:36.250 --> 00:49:39.040
- You're so right. It's pretty.
- [Mum] I wasn't going to say.

798
00:49:39.041 --> 00:49:40.624
but you can't expect
me not to notice.

799
00:49:40.625 --> 00:49:41.999
[Nick] You're
being ridiculous.

800
00:49:42.000 --> 00:49:43.749
[Mum] Why isn't William
keeping tabs on you?

801
00:49:43.750 --> 00:49:45.165
I was in the ring.

802
00:49:45.166 --> 00:49:47.749
You don't get cuts like
these wearing gloves. Nick.

803
00:49:47.750 --> 00:49:49.790
so stop lying to me.

804
00:49:49.791 --> 00:49:52.999
Mum won't let Nick come
to my football match.

805
00:49:53.000 --> 00:49:55.665
[Mum] No street fights.
no racing and no drugs.

806
00:49:55.666 --> 00:49:57.374
or you lose your
privileges with Maddie.

807
00:49:57.375 --> 00:49:58.499
OK. this wasn't my fault.

808
00:49:58.500 --> 00:50:01.750
[Mum] No. no. no. no. no.
no. Your body is your own.

809
00:50:02.583 --> 00:50:04.583
I'm not gonna deal
with this shit.

810
00:50:05.958 --> 00:50:07.958
I'm gonna go get a drink.

811
00:50:09.375 --> 00:50:10.583
[chuckles softly]

812
00:50:13.375 --> 00:50:14.540
[Mum] Here.

813
00:50:14.541 --> 00:50:15.875
[Noah] Thank you.

814
00:50:20.125 --> 00:50:22.082
He won't be far.

815
00:50:22.083 --> 00:50:26.208
He just... needs
to blow off steam.

816
00:50:28.041 --> 00:50:30.999
I think it's great you
two have reconnected.

817
00:50:31.000 --> 00:50:32.291
Oh. well...

818
00:50:33.458 --> 00:50:36.333
Would have been nice if I hadn't
had to leave in the first place.

819
00:50:38.250 --> 00:50:39.915
I. um...

820
00:50:39.916 --> 00:50:43.458
I was... well. <i>am</i> an alcoholic.

821
00:50:44.500 --> 00:50:45.583
Did he tell you that?

822
00:50:49.250 --> 00:50:52.166
I left him and his dad
because I needed to get well.

823
00:50:53.625 --> 00:50:56.208
During my treatment. I tried
to reach out to Nick. but...

824
00:50:57.125 --> 00:50:58.458
he. er...

825
00:51:00.791 --> 00:51:02.291
He wasn't ready.

826
00:51:05.666 --> 00:51:06.665
So for years.

827
00:51:06.666 --> 00:51:09.500
Nick has been trying to deal
with all this by himself.

828
00:51:10.750 --> 00:51:11.791
[sighs]

829
00:51:12.416 --> 00:51:18.208
All the anger he feels for me
comes out through his fists.

830
00:51:20.250 --> 00:51:21.625
Or on the road.

831
00:51:24.333 --> 00:51:26.874
Families can be
complicated. can't they?

832
00:51:26.875 --> 00:51:29.541
- Welcome to ours. Noah.
- [chuckles]

833
00:51:37.125 --> 00:51:38.250
[door opens]

834
00:51:39.541 --> 00:51:40.957
[door closes]

835
00:51:40.958 --> 00:51:43.041
[footsteps approach]

836
00:51:49.416 --> 00:51:51.666
- You OK?
- Yeah.

837
00:51:53.541 --> 00:51:55.625
Maybe. I don't know. er...

838
00:51:56.125 --> 00:51:58.499
I'm sorry. you've
got your own shit.

839
00:51:58.500 --> 00:52:01.207
Yeah. but Dan's thousands
of miles away. so...

840
00:52:01.208 --> 00:52:02.457
[Nick chuckles]

841
00:52:02.458 --> 00:52:06.041
Which is lucky. or I'd
punch his lights out.

842
00:52:06.958 --> 00:52:10.166
Which wouldn't improve the
situation with your mom.

843
00:52:12.541 --> 00:52:14.000
I don't care.

844
00:52:18.375 --> 00:52:20.583
If you were mine. I'd
never let anyone hurt you.

845
00:52:26.083 --> 00:52:27.583
[sighs]

846
00:52:37.375 --> 00:52:38.583
[softly] Nick...

847
00:52:44.458 --> 00:52:47.125
I want you more than
I've ever wanted anyone.

848
00:53:06.833 --> 00:53:08.041
[Maddie] Nick?

849
00:53:09.208 --> 00:53:10.916
Is that you?

850
00:53:13.458 --> 00:53:14.916
[Nick] I'll be right there.

851
00:53:20.791 --> 00:53:22.125
Shit. Noah.

852
00:53:26.375 --> 00:53:28.541
What the hell are
you doing to me?

853
00:53:41.333 --> 00:53:42.833
See you in the morning.

854
00:53:45.250 --> 00:53:46.457
[Mum] Please. stop.

855
00:53:46.458 --> 00:53:48.374
[Maddie] But I want
him to be there.

856
00:53:48.375 --> 00:53:51.041
[Mum] Maddie. we
spoke about this.

857
00:53:53.583 --> 00:53:54.832
OK. I'll see you very soon. OK?

858
00:53:54.833 --> 00:53:57.000
And I will come and watch
you play. I promise.

859
00:53:58.125 --> 00:54:00.582
Yeah? Give me a hug.

860
00:54:00.583 --> 00:54:02.750
All right. come on. run along.

861
00:54:03.500 --> 00:54:05.624
- I'll see you later Mum. yeah?
- Hey. Hey.

862
00:54:05.625 --> 00:54:08.165
This is your last chance.
No more illegal fights.

863
00:54:08.166 --> 00:54:09.374
All right. I've got it.

864
00:54:09.375 --> 00:54:11.457
- OK. Look. you understand?
- Yes.

865
00:54:11.458 --> 00:54:13.957
[Mum] Maddie loves you so much.
You don't want to let her down.

866
00:54:13.958 --> 00:54:15.082
[Nick scoffs]

867
00:54:15.083 --> 00:54:16.665
[Mum] Oh...

868
00:54:16.666 --> 00:54:18.708
[Nick] Such a hypocrite.

869
00:54:20.666 --> 00:54:22.375
- [car door closes]
- Let's go.

870
00:54:25.833 --> 00:54:27.833
[engine roars]

871
00:54:36.458 --> 00:54:38.582
[Noah] Er. do you
have plans later?

872
00:54:38.583 --> 00:54:40.415
- Do you wanna. like. watch a...
- Yeah.

873
00:54:40.416 --> 00:54:44.083
Yeah. I'm busy. Sorry.

874
00:54:51.916 --> 00:54:53.207
Hey. what's... what's going on?

875
00:54:53.208 --> 00:54:55.082
Look. I just need to
stay out of trouble.

876
00:54:55.083 --> 00:54:56.250
[scoffs]

877
00:54:57.250 --> 00:54:59.416
And I'm trouble. right?

878
00:55:03.875 --> 00:55:05.125
[scoffs]

879
00:55:06.000 --> 00:55:07.665
You're not afraid your
mom's gonna find out

880
00:55:07.666 --> 00:55:10.749
about your fight with Ronnie?
About the underground racing?

881
00:55:10.750 --> 00:55:12.541
I didn't race. you did.

882
00:55:13.625 --> 00:55:15.583
And now I have to fight
Ronnie because of that.

883
00:55:32.833 --> 00:55:34.458
[car boot closes]

884
00:55:42.250 --> 00:55:45.333
[movie plays through headphones]

885
00:55:47.041 --> 00:55:48.125
[distant thud]

886
00:55:55.125 --> 00:55:57.000
- Hello?
- [faint noise]

887
00:55:58.250 --> 00:55:59.333
Mom?!

888
00:56:03.708 --> 00:56:05.583
[quiet clattering]

889
00:56:17.500 --> 00:56:18.665
- Surprise!
- Oh. my God!

890
00:56:18.666 --> 00:56:20.290
- I'm sorry.
- Oh. my God.

891
00:56:20.291 --> 00:56:21.583
[door opens]

892
00:56:22.291 --> 00:56:23.666
Oh!

893
00:56:24.708 --> 00:56:26.999
Oh. I missed the surprise.

894
00:56:27.000 --> 00:56:28.749
[Dan chuckles nervously]

895
00:56:28.750 --> 00:56:30.083
Are you surprised?

896
00:56:31.458 --> 00:56:32.541
Yeah.

897
00:56:34.375 --> 00:56:37.540
That's all right. Martin.
The keys were in my bag.

898
00:56:37.541 --> 00:56:38.750
I know!

899
00:56:39.708 --> 00:56:41.290
Your mom invited me to visit.

900
00:56:41.291 --> 00:56:43.583
She said that maybe
you missed me?

901
00:56:44.333 --> 00:56:47.040
- Hug?
- Get out.

902
00:56:47.041 --> 00:56:51.082
Noah. please. look. I made a
mistake. OK? Never ever again.

903
00:56:51.083 --> 00:56:52.540
- Trust me.
- Trust you?

904
00:56:52.541 --> 00:56:54.582
[Dan] Yes. I wouldn't be
here if I didn't want this.

905
00:56:54.583 --> 00:56:55.665
Dan. come on!

906
00:56:55.666 --> 00:56:58.749
Oh. my God. Noah. I was
so cut up when you left.

907
00:56:58.750 --> 00:57:01.250
OK? I lost my girlfriend
and my best friend.

908
00:57:02.375 --> 00:57:05.582
I admit that what I did
was a colossal mistake.

909
00:57:05.583 --> 00:57:07.750
for which I deserve
to be chastised.

910
00:57:09.250 --> 00:57:13.250
But don't punish <i>us.</i>
OK? What we have.

911
00:57:14.083 --> 00:57:15.833
We're so good. Noah.

912
00:57:20.416 --> 00:57:21.625
[sighs]

913
00:57:22.750 --> 00:57:24.915
I didn't wanna have to give
you up without a fight.

914
00:57:24.916 --> 00:57:26.791
but if you want me to
leave. then I will.

915
00:57:28.541 --> 00:57:30.082
Colossal and chastised?

916
00:57:30.083 --> 00:57:31.332
[chuckles softly]

917
00:57:31.333 --> 00:57:33.082
- I might have looked them up.
- Pathetic.

918
00:57:33.083 --> 00:57:35.082
OK.

919
00:57:35.083 --> 00:57:38.416
If you stay. it's as a
friend. A shitty friend.

920
00:57:39.041 --> 00:57:40.125
OK?

921
00:57:46.250 --> 00:57:47.583
[sighs deeply]

922
00:57:50.166 --> 00:57:51.541
It's a nice house.

923
00:57:56.000 --> 00:57:58.874
[Dan] <i>We should get out. Go
and see Buckingham Palace</i>

924
00:57:58.875 --> 00:58:00.874
and the wheel. and
Windsor Castle.

925
00:58:00.875 --> 00:58:03.165
I don't know. London stuff.

926
00:58:03.166 --> 00:58:05.290
Oh. thank you. Thank
you so much. Emily.

927
00:58:05.291 --> 00:58:07.291
- That was delicious.
- Mm-hmm.

928
00:58:13.166 --> 00:58:14.540
[sighs]

929
00:58:14.541 --> 00:58:16.166
I didn't sleep last night.

930
00:58:16.875 --> 00:58:18.125
Texting Haley?

931
00:58:18.916 --> 00:58:20.957
[exhales] Fair.

932
00:58:20.958 --> 00:58:23.500
No. I... Look.

933
00:58:24.958 --> 00:58:28.749
I'll do anything. OK.
to make this work.

934
00:58:28.750 --> 00:58:31.041
I just want you back. Noah.

935
00:58:35.250 --> 00:58:36.374
[Dan] Hey.

936
00:58:36.375 --> 00:58:38.499
N-No. we weren't...

937
00:58:38.500 --> 00:58:41.082
I think your brother can read
the room. Noah. [chuckles]

938
00:58:41.083 --> 00:58:43.583
How you doing? I'm
Dan. Noah's boyfriend.

939
00:58:44.333 --> 00:58:45.625
Cool shirt.

940
00:58:47.333 --> 00:58:49.999
Yeah. "Life moves pretty fast.

941
00:58:50.000 --> 00:58:52.040
If you don't stop and look
around once in a while.

942
00:58:52.041 --> 00:58:53.500
you could miss it." [chuckles]

943
00:58:54.500 --> 00:58:57.499
No? It's. er. <i>Ferris
Bueller's Day Off.</i>

944
00:58:57.500 --> 00:58:58.666
Yeah. I know.

945
00:59:00.958 --> 00:59:02.750
[Dan exhales. chuckles]

946
00:59:07.833 --> 00:59:08.916
[Dan scoffs]

947
00:59:11.625 --> 00:59:13.125
What a dick. [chuckles]

948
00:59:15.041 --> 00:59:17.500
Wait. is that the. er...
the guy from the photos?

949
00:59:20.541 --> 00:59:21.916
It is. isn't it?

950
00:59:23.708 --> 00:59:25.832
OK. Well. er...

951
00:59:25.833 --> 00:59:28.125
That'll never work.

952
00:59:48.208 --> 00:59:49.916
[Nick] Back together. then?

953
00:59:50.291 --> 00:59:51.457
Kiss me.

954
00:59:51.458 --> 00:59:54.290
[♪ "Beggin for Thread" by Banks]

955
00:59:54.291 --> 00:59:55.458
Wait.

956
00:59:59.000 --> 01:00:00.208
Not here.

957
01:00:01.750 --> 01:00:03.790
<i>♪ So I got edges
that scratch... ♪</i>

958
01:00:03.791 --> 01:00:04.958
Here.

959
01:00:06.250 --> 01:00:08.707
<i>♪ And sometimes. I
don't got a filter ♪</i>

960
01:00:08.708 --> 01:00:11.457
<i>♪ But I'm so tired of eating ♪</i>

961
01:00:11.458 --> 01:00:14.833
<i>♪ All of my misspoken words ♪</i>

962
01:00:16.958 --> 01:00:18.457
Here.

963
01:00:18.458 --> 01:00:22.832
<i>♪ I know my disposition
gets confusing ♪</i>

964
01:00:22.833 --> 01:00:28.875
<i>♪ My disproportionate reactions
fuse with my eager state ♪</i>

965
01:00:29.666 --> 01:00:33.999
<i>♪ That's why you wanna come
out and play with me... ♪</i>

966
01:00:34.000 --> 01:00:36.041
- Here.
<i>- ♪ Yeah ♪</i>

967
01:00:40.500 --> 01:00:44.582
<i>♪ Why? ♪</i>

968
01:00:44.583 --> 01:00:49.457
<i>♪ Why? ♪</i>

969
01:00:49.458 --> 01:00:50.750
Don't hurt him.

970
01:00:53.291 --> 01:00:54.707
But make him leave.

971
01:00:54.708 --> 01:00:56.165
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

972
01:00:56.166 --> 01:00:58.790
<i>♪ Stooped down and out ♪</i>

973
01:00:58.791 --> 01:01:00.999
<i>♪ You got me
begging for thread ♪</i>

974
01:01:01.000 --> 01:01:06.000
<i>♪ To sew this hole up that
you ripped in my head... ♪</i>

975
01:01:09.166 --> 01:01:11.374
Hey. buddy. how's it going?

976
01:01:11.375 --> 01:01:13.374
You haven't seen my
girlfriend around. have you?

977
01:01:13.375 --> 01:01:15.582
Think you lost the privilege
of calling her that

978
01:01:15.583 --> 01:01:17.207
